# Terminology — Zero Tolerance (厳守)

**`docs/explanation/terminology.md` is the single, canonical source of truth for every
identifier.** No other doc or code comment overrides it.

Before writing code, OpenAPI, DB schema, migrations, tests, MCP catalog, or docs, **read
the registry** and use the exact registered spelling.

## Merge blockers (MUST)

- Typos of registered terms
- Spelling / case / pluralization variants (e.g. `contactForm` in JSON where `contact_form`
  is registered; `Repo`/`Service` suffix where `RepositoryInterface`/`UseCase` is registered)
- Synonyms of a registered term (`inquiry` / `message` / `lead` for `submission`)
- A new identifier (entity, field, status, slug, `operationId`, env var, role, class)
  without a registry row **in the same PR**
- Renaming a shipped `operationId` or Problem Details slug

## Common mistakes

| Wrong | Correct (see terminology.md) |
|---|---|
| `contactForm` in JSON | `contact_form` |
| `inquiry` / `message` / `lead` | `submission` or `submission_note` |
| `Controller` / `Service` / `Manager` / `Repo` suffix | `Handler` / `UseCase` / `RepositoryInterface` |
| locale key other than `ja` / `en` | `ja` / `en` only (ADR 0011) |
| invented role string | `superadmin` / `admin` / `editor` (ADR 0006) |
| ad-hoc problem URI | `https://nene-contact.dev/problems/{slug}` |

When in doubt, match the registry exactly — do not guess, do not invent a variant. A
deliberate rename requires an ADR (self-authority, ADR 0012 model).
